  "time_ut": 1662368922,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db8\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0db4\u0ddd\u0dc2\u0dab\u0dba \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0d9a \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A two-day debate on the malnutrition of children in this country",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A two-day debate will be held in Parliament tomorrow (6) and the day after (7) regarding the report issued by UNICEF regarding the malnutrition of children and mothers in Sri Lanka.",
        "The proposal for the debate is presented by Samagi Jana Balawegaya Party.",
        "Meanwhile, the Parliament has decided the Committee on Parliamentary Affairs to meet from tomorrow (6) to the 9th.",
        "The Social Security Contribution Tax Bill and the Regulations under the Import and Export (Control) Act are scheduled to be adopted without debate tomorrow (6) from 10.30 am to 10.45 am.",
        "The Secretary General of the Parliament Mr. Dhammika Dasanayake said that the debate on the adjournment of the Assembly regarding the mid-year fiscal situation report (for the year 2022) will be held on the 8th.",
        "Tomorrow (6), tomorrow (7) and next day (8) from 9.30 am to 10.30 am have been reserved for the questions that require oral answers from the MPs. This is the first opportunity to ask questions that require oral answers in the new assembly.",
        "Two Industrial Disputes (Amendment) Bills (130 and 132) and the Workers' Protection (Special Provisions) (Amendment) Bill are to be passed without debate on the 8th from 10.30 am to 11.00 am.",
        "Meanwhile, the Committee on Parliamentary Affairs has decided to hold the condolence debate on Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna's Polonnaru District Member of Parliament Mr. Amarakirthi Athukorala who was killed by a violent group in Nittambuwa on Friday 9th.",
        "Thus, the debate will be held that day from 9.30 am to 4.30 pm."
      ],
